LOB_Description: Golden Guinea Breweries Plc Was Incorporated On 26Th September 1962, Under The Name Of Independence Brewery Limited By The Then Eastern Nigeria Development Corporation (Endc), The Investment Arm Of The Government Of The Former Eastern Region Of Nigeria. The Construction Of The First Brewery Commenced On 1St November 1961 And Was Completed On 30 September 1963. On 18Th September 1963 Brewing Of Larger Beer Commenced And In November Of The Same Year Golden Guinea Larger Beer Was Launched Into The Nigerian Market. It Began Producing Its Second Product Eagle Stout In 1967 Thereby Becoming One Of The Two Breweries Producing Stout In Nigeria At That Time. On 6Th May 1971, The Company Changed Its Name To Golden Guinea Breweries Limited. As A Result Of The Reconstitution Of Nigeria Into States, The Ownership Of Golden Guinea Breweries Limited Passed To The East Central State Government And On To The Imo State Government In 1976. Golden Guniea Breweries Became A Publicly-Quoted Company Listed On The Nigerian Stock Exchange In 1978 When Imo State Government'S Holding Was Reduced To 50%. In 1983 The Shareholding Of Imo State Was Reduced Again To 25.5%. With The Creation Of Abia State Out Of The Former Imo State In 1991 The 25.5% Shareholding By Imo State Was Shared. The Company Has About 25,000 Nigerian Shareholders Holding 80% Of The Company'S Equity While 20% Is Held By Non-Nigerian Associations And Citizens. The Company Receives Technical Assistance From Holsten Brauerei Ag Of Hamburg Especially In The Areas Of New Mproved Production Proceses And Equipment, Research Into Raw Materials, Constant Quality Assurance And Innovative Marketing Technique
